nitiatives at Human Rights Watch, toldThe Independentthat France's ban on hijabs for sportspeople infringes the Olympic Charter.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 872, \"end\": 884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minky_Worden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Minky Worden\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minky_Worden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minky_Worden\"}, {\"begin\": 920, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Human_Rights_Watch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Human Rights Watch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Human_Rights_Watch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Human_Rights_Watch\"}, {\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997412873737871, \"rank\": 0.0001706358241940644, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"director\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"global initiatives\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"hijabs\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"sportspeople\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Charter\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said: \\\"The effect of France's exclusionary hijab bans across many sports is that many women and girls from the Olympics' own host nation are discriminated against, excluded, and prevented from playing, practising and competing in sports they love and excel at.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1061, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997412873737871, \"rank\": 0.0001706358241940644, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The effect\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"many sports\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"many women\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics' own host nation\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a violation of both the Olympic Charter, which says 'sport is a human right,' and also the new International Olympic Committee Human Rights framework.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1461, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a violation\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1322}, {\"ngram\": \"both the Olympic Charter\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1350}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"a human right\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These French women athletes are shut out of competitive sport in their country and there is no access to remedy available to them.\\\"\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1469, \"end\": 1475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9357580173867852, \"rank\": 0.06789520768888008, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"competitive sport\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"their country\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"no access\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"remedy\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1574}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During a press briefing on Tuesday, Ms Worden said the hijab ban has driven some French athletes to leave the country or contemplate moving abroad.\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Lorimer_Worden\", \"scor